SIMPLE: flatly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flatly
<hw>Flat"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a flat manner;
evenly; horizontally; without spirit; dully; frigidly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that does the works of religion slowly, <qex>flatly</qex>, and
without appetite.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>peremptorily; positively; plainly;
forthrightly.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧He <xex>flatly</xex> refused his aid.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir P. Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>flatmate</ent>⟦br⟧
